Although there have been a number of projects that have included concepts of commonsense psychology as part of a larger lexical-semantic resource, e.g. the Berkeley FrameNet Project (Baker et al., 1998), none have attempted to achieve a high degree of breadth or depth over the sorts of expressions that people use to refer to mental states and processes.
